  <summary>2/9/1999--Introduced.
Honest Balanced Budget Act of 1999 - Declares that the receipts and disbursements of the social security trust funds included in the gross Federal debt shall not be: (1) included in the Federal budget baseline for any fiscal year; and (2) counted as new budget authority, outlays, receipts, or deficit or surplus for purposes of offsetting any tax decrease and any spending increase.</summary>
